\section{Trigonometry}

%claude:
The trigonometric functions ([[sin]], [[cos]], [[tan]],
[[atan]], [[atan2]]) use polynomial approximations from
Hart et al.'s tables. The shared [[sinus]] helper first
reduces the argument to the range $[0, \pi/4]$ using the
periodicity of sin/cos, then evaluates a rational polynomial
$p(x)/q(x)$. The coefficients (p0--p4, q0--q3) are chosen
to give double-precision accuracy over this range.

\subsection{Direct functions}

<<function [[cos]]>>=
double
cos(double arg)
{
    if(arg < 0)
        arg = -arg;
    return sinus(arg, 1);
}
@

<<function [[sin]]>>=
double
sin(double arg)
{
    return sinus(arg, 0);
}
@




